            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-11-07T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-11-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.24/10–2447: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Belgium</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-11-07T19:00:00-05:00">November 7, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1615. <gloss target="#t_reurtel1">Reurtel</gloss> 1659 Oct 24.<note n="21" xml:id="d195fn1">For text, see A–505, November 3, to Buenos Aires, <ref target="#pg_232">p. 232</ref>.</note> For your confidential <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> current shipments tanks from Belg to
                    Argentina are within requirements, which Army expects to recognize for Argentina
                    under Western Hemisphere Defense Program. For this reason and because Belg’s
                    urgent need gram Dept does not wish raise any objection continued exchange tanks
                    and cereals. Please arrange however give us notice all tank shipments as far in
                    advance as possible.</p>
                <p>Sent Brussels, repeated Buenos Aires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
